# shell/mesh-repos.list — paths your `claude` invocations should auto-redirect
# from. When the cwd matches any prefix below, mesh-guard.zsh offers to `cd`
# you to $DOTFILES_DIR before running claude (so the memory/PROJECT_STATUS
# loads correctly).
#
# To activate: rename this file to `shell/mesh-repos.list` and list one
# absolute path per line. Comments (#) and blank lines ignored.
#
# Without an active mesh-repos.list file, the mesh-guard `claude()` wrapper
# is a no-op pass-through (zero effect — just runs `command claude "$@"`).
#
# Format: one path per line. `~` and `$HOME` are expanded.
# Sandbox: any cwd whose canonical path begins with the listed prefix triggers
# the redirect prompt. To match a single subtree, list its parent.

# Examples (uncomment + adapt to YOUR repos):
#
# $HOME/dev-bootstrap
# $HOME/dotfiles-template
# $HOME/work/some-project
